I have here... I found this in the apartment.

1377
01:17:29,080 --> 01:17:32,600
Black soap. She used to wash her face
800 times a day with black soap.

1378
01:17:32,800 --> 01:17:34,680
Don't ask me why.

1379
01:17:34,800 --> 01:17:37,080
Why don't you go out with other women?

1380
01:17:37,200 --> 01:17:40,680
Well, I tried. But it's...
you know, it's very depressing.

1381
01:17:40,800 --> 01:17:43,600
This always happens to me.
Quick! Get a broom!

1382
01:17:44,600 --> 01:17:48,200
What are you making such a big deal
about? They're only lobsters.

1383
01:17:48,280 --> 01:17:51,200
You're a grown man.
You know how to pick up a lobster.

1384
01:17:51,280 --> 01:17:54,480
- I'm not myself since I stopped smoking.
- When did you quit?

1385
01:17:54,680 --> 01:17:55,680
16 years ago.

1386
01:17:55,880 --> 01:17:57,280
What do you mean?

1387
01:17:57,400 --> 01:17:58,600
Mean?

1388
01:17:59,400 --> 01:18:02,800
You stopped smoking 16 years ago.
Is that what you said?

1389
01:18:04,080 --> 01:18:06,280
I don't understand.

1390
01:18:06,400 --> 01:18:08,400
Are you joking or what?

1391
01:18:19,800 --> 01:18:21,680
Central Park's turning green.

1392
01:18:21,880 --> 01:18:24,680
Yeah. I saw that lunatic
that we used to see

1393
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:28,800
with the pinwheel hat,
you know, and the roller skates.

1394
01:18:29,000 --> 01:18:31,400
Listen, I... I want you to come back here.

1395
01:18:32,400 --> 01:18:35,880
Well... Then I'm gonna
come out there and get you.

1396
01:18:39,400 --> 01:18:42,400
What do you mean, where am l?
Where do you think I am?

1397
01:18:42,480 --> 01:18:45,200
I'm at the Los Angeles airport. I flew in.

1398
01:18:45,280 --> 01:18:47,600
I... Well, I flew in to see you.

1399
01:18:48,600 --> 01:18:51,800
Hey, listen. Can we not
debate this on the telephone?

1400
01:18:52,000 --> 01:18:54,280
Because I feel that I got a temperature.

1401
01:18:54,480 --> 01:18:59,080
And I'm getting my chronic Los Angeles
nausea already. I don't feel so good.

1402
01:18:59,280 --> 01:19:03,600
<i>Wherever you wanna meet. I don't care.
I'll drive in. I rented a car.</i>

1403
01:19:04,280 --> 01:19:06,400
<i>I'm driving. What do you...</i>

1404
01:19:06,480 --> 01:19:09,400
<i>What, is that such a miracle?
I'm driving myself.</i>

1405
01:19:24,880 --> 01:19:28,680
I'm gonna have the alfalfa sprouts and...

1406
01:19:28,800 --> 01:19:30,680
a plate of mashed yeast.

1407
01:19:49,800 --> 01:19:51,680
You look very pretty.

1408
01:19:51,800 --> 01:19:55,280
Oh, no. I just lost a little weight, that's all.

1409
01:19:59,280 --> 01:20:02,280
Well... you look nice.

1410
01:20:02,400 --> 01:20:06,000
I've been thinking about it,
and I think that we should get married.

1411
01:20:06,080 --> 01:20:07,480
Oh, Alvy. Come on.

1412
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:11,280
Why? You wanna live out here?

1413
01:20:11,400 --> 01:20:13,480
It's like living in Munchkin Land.

1414
01:20:14,080 --> 01:20:16,880
What do you mean?
It's perfectly fine out here.

1415
01:20:17,080 --> 01:20:19,000
I mean, Tony's very nice.

1416
01:20:19,200 --> 01:20:23,200
And... well, I meet people
and I go to parties and we play tennis.

1417
01:20:23,400 --> 01:20:26,280
I mean, that's a very big step for me,
you know.

1418
01:20:26,480 --> 01:20:28,680
I mean, I'm able to enjoy people more.

1419
01:20:29,680 --> 01:20:32,400
So... you're not gonna
come back to New York?

1420
01:20:32,480 --> 01:20:36,200
What's so great about New York? It's
a dying city. You read 'Death in Venice'.

1421
01:20:36,400 --> 01:20:39,080
You didn't read 'Death in Venice'
till I bought it for you.

1422
01:20:39,280 --> 01:20:42,800
That's right. You only gave me books
with the word ''death'' in the title.

1423
01:20:42,880 --> 01:20:45,080
Cos it's an important issue.

1424
01:20:45,200 --> 01:20:47,480
Alvy, you're incapable of enjoying life.

1425
01:20:47,600 --> 01:20:50,480
You're like New York City.
You're just this person.

1426
01:20:50,600 --> 01:20:53,000
You're like this island unto yourself.

1427
01:20:53,200 --> 01:20:55,800
I can't enjoy anything
unless everybody is.

1428
01:20:56,000 --> 01:21:00,280
If one guy is starving someplace,
that's... it puts a crimp in my evening.

1429
01:21:02,480 --> 01:21:04,480
So you wanna get married or what?

1430
01:21:06,280 --> 01:21:08,680
No. We're friends.

1431
01:21:08,800 --> 01:21:10,680
I wanna remain friends.

1432
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:13,800
OK.

1433
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:15,600
Check, please!

1434
01:21:15,680 --> 01:21:17,800
You're mad, aren't you?

1435
01:21:18,000 --> 01:21:21,280
Yes, of course I'm mad.
Because you love me. I know that.

1436
01:21:21,480 --> 01:21:26,000
Alvy, I can't say that that's true
at this point in my life. I really can't.

1437
01:21:26,080 --> 01:21:28,080
You know how wonderful you are.

1438
01:21:28,200 --> 01:21:32,600
You know you're the reason that I got out
of my room and that I was able to sing

1439
01:21:32,680 --> 01:21:35,880
and get more in touch
with my feelings and all that crap.

1440
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:39,480
Anyway, look, I don't wanna...
Listen, listen, listen...

1441
01:21:40,680 --> 01:21:42,680
So what are you up to anyway, huh?

1442
01:21:44,800 --> 01:21:48,600
The usual, you know. I'm trying to write.
I'm working on a play.

1443
01:21:49,000 --> 01:21:53,000
So what are you saying? You're not
coming back to New York with me?

1444
01:21:53,880 --> 01:21:55,880
No. Look...

1445
01:21:57,400 --> 01:21:58,800
I gotta go.

1446
01:21:58,880 --> 01:22:01,400
- I flew 3,000 miles to see you.
- I'm late.

1447
01:22:01,480 --> 01:22:04,400
Air miles. You know what
that does to my stomach?

1448
01:22:04,480 --> 01:22:07,480
It's a hectic time for Tony.
The Grammies are tonight.

1449
01:22:07,600 --> 01:22:10,400
- The what?
- He's got a lot of records up for awards.

1450
01:22:10,600 --> 01:22:13,480
They give awards for that music?
I thought just earplugs.

1451
01:22:13,680 --> 01:22:16,400
Just forget it!
Let's just forget the conversation.

1452
01:22:16,600 --> 01:22:19,880
Awards! They do nothing
but give out awards! I can't believe it.

1453
01:22:20,000 --> 01:22:22,680
Greatest fascist dictator - Adolf Hitler.

1454
01:22:51,080 --> 01:22:56,080
I know what you're gonna say. I'm not a
great driver. I have some problems with...

1455
01:22:56,200 --> 01:22:58,080
Can I see your licence, please?

1456
01:22:58,280 --> 01:23:00,800
Just don't get angry or anything, cos I...

1457
01:23:01,000 --> 01:23:02,880
I have my licence here.

1458
01:23:03,000 --> 01:23:05,000
It's a rented car and I... I...

1459
01:23:05,080 --> 01:23:06,080
Here.

1460
01:23:06,200 --> 01:23:08,080
Don't give me your life...

1461
01:23:08,200 --> 01:23:09,080
story.

1462
01:23:09,280 --> 01:23:11,200
Just pick up the licence.

1463
01:23:11,400 --> 01:23:15,600
You have to ask nicely cos I've had
an extremely rough day. My girlfriend...

1464
01:23:15,680 --> 01:23:17,680
Just give me the licence, please.

1465
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:22,200
Since you put it that way,
it's hard for me to refuse.

1466
01:23:22,400 --> 01:23:24,880
I have a terrific problem with authority.

1467
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,680
It's not your fault. Don't take it personal.

1468
01:23:35,400 --> 01:23:37,280
So long, fellas. Keep in touch.

1469
01:23:46,680 --> 01:23:50,480
Imagine my surprise
when I got your call, Max.

1470
01:23:50,600 --> 01:23:53,680
Yeah. I had the feeling
that I got you at a bad moment.

1471
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:56,000
I heard high-pitched squealing.

1472
01:23:56,200 --> 01:23:58,080
Twins, Max.

1473
01:23:58,200 --> 01:24:00,280
16-year-olds.

1474
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:05,000
Can you imagine
the mathematical possibilities of that?

1475
01:24:05,200 --> 01:24:09,000
You're an actor, Max. You should be
doing Shakespeare in the Park.

1476
01:24:09,200 --> 01:24:11,880
I did Shakespeare in the Park, Max.
I got mugged.

1477
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:16,480
I was playing Richard II, and two guys
with leather jackets stole my leotard.

1478
01:24:20,880 --> 01:24:23,280
Max, are we driving through plutonium?

1479
01:24:24,080 --> 01:24:26,000
It keeps out the alpha rays, Max.

1480
01:24:26,200 --> 01:24:28,080
You don't get old.

1481
01:24:29,880 --> 01:24:33,000
You're a thinking person.
How can you choose this lifestyle?

1482
01:24:33,200 --> 01:24:35,680
What is so incredibly great
about New York?

1483
01:24:35,880 --> 01:24:38,680
It's a dying city.
You read 'Death in Venice'.

1484
01:24:38,880 --> 01:24:41,080
You didn't read it till I gave it to you.

1485
01:24:41,200 --> 01:24:43,400
You only give me books
with ''death'' in the title.

1486
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:47,200
- It's an important issue.
- You are totally incapable of enjoying life.

1487
01:24:47,400 --> 01:24:49,680
You're like New York. You're an island.

1488
01:24:49,880 --> 01:24:53,480
OK. lf that's all that we've been
through together means to you,

1489
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:57,000
I guess it's better if we just
say goodbye, once and for all.

1490
01:24:57,080 --> 01:25:01,280
You know, it's funny, after all the serious
talks and passionate moments,

1491
01:25:01,400 --> 01:25:05,200
that it ends here, in a health-food
restaurant on Sunset Boulevard.

1492
01:25:05,400 --> 01:25:07,480
Goodbye, Sunny.

1493
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:09,080
Wait.

1494
01:25:09,200 --> 01:25:11,080
I'm gonna go with you.

1495
01:25:12,200 --> 01:25:14,080
I love you.

1496
01:25:17,080 --> 01:25:19,400
What do you want? lt was my first play.

1497
01:25:19,480 --> 01:25:23,600
You know how you're always trying to
get things to come out perfect in art

1498
01:25:23,800 --> 01:25:26,000
because it's real difficult in life.

1499
01:25:26,200 --> 01:25:30,080
Interestingly, however,
I did run into Annie again.

1500
01:25:30,200 --> 01:25:32,800
It was on the Upper West Side
of Manhattan.

1501
01:25:32,880 --> 01:25:36,200
<i>She had moved back to New York.
She was living in SoHo with some guy.</i>

1502
01:25:36,280 --> 01:25:40,000
<i>And when I met her, she was dragging
him in to see The Sorrow and the Pity,</i>

1503
01:25:40,200 --> 01:25:43,000
<i>which I counted as a personal triumph.</i>

1504
01:25:43,080 --> 01:25:46,000
<i>Annie and I had lunch
sometime after that and...</i>

1505
01:25:46,200 --> 01:25:48,400
<i>just kicked around old times.</i>

1506
01:25:49,480 --> 01:25:55,080
<i> Just to have my arms</i>

1507
01:25:55,480 --> 01:26:00,000
<i> Around you</i>

1508
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:06,200
<i> Still the thrill that it was</i>

1509
01:26:06,400 --> 01:26:10,480
<i> The day I found you</i>

1510
01:26:10,600 --> 01:26:15,480
<i> Seems like</i>

1511
01:26:16,800 --> 01:26:22,600
<i> Old times</i>

1512
01:26:23,800 --> 01:26:30,600
<i> Dinner dates and flowers</i>

1513
01:26:30,800 --> 01:26:34,600
<i> Old times</i>

1514
01:26:34,800 --> 01:26:37,880
<i>After that, it got pretty late
and we both had to go.</i>

1515
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:42,280
<i>But it was great seeing Annie again.
I realised what a terrific person she was</i>

1516
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:45,000
<i>and how much fun it was
just knowing her.</i>

1517
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:47,800
<i>And I thought of that old joke, you know.</i>

1518
01:26:47,880 --> 01:26:50,880
<i>This guy goes to a psychiatrist and says,</i>

1519
01:26:51,080 --> 01:26:54,680
<i>''Doc, my brother's crazy.
He thinks he's a chicken. ''</i>

1520
01:26:54,880 --> 01:26:58,200
<i>And the doctor says,
''Well, why don't you turn him in?''</i>

1521
01:26:58,280 --> 01:27:01,280
<i>And the guy says,
''I would, but I need the eggs. ''</i>

1522
01:27:01,400 --> 01:27:05,680
<i>Well, I guess that's pretty much now
how I feel about relationships.</i>

1523
01:27:05,800 --> 01:27:10,600
<i>You know, they're totally irrational
and crazy and absurd and...</i>

1524
01:27:10,680 --> 01:27:16,800
<i>But I guess we keep going through it
because most of us need the eggs.</i>
